A survey conducted by Ipsos in conjunction with 24-hour news channel eNCA between April 21 and May 22 has shown that only 18% of African National Congress voters support President Jacob Zuma s continued stay in power.The survey polled about 3 500 adults in the said period, and its results indicated that 62% of the governing party s voters disapproved of Zuma amid a string of scandals that have dogged his time in office and calls by the ANC s alliance partners, Cosatu and the SA Communist Party, for him to step down. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on citizen.co.za